== Comparison with Tang China == Unlike Japan, Tang China managed its capital {{ill|Chang'an|ja|長安}} through regular provincial systems like {{ill|Kuannei Dao|ja|関内道}}, which supervised {{ill|Yongzhou|ja|雍州}} under its jurisdiction. Additionally, tasks like policing and tax collection were divided among multiple layers of officials. The Kyōshiki's centralized model reflected Japan's adaptation of Tang principles to a smaller, more urbanized environment.{{ref|市川 2009, P216-264}}
